#--------------------------

"When the fox preacheth, then beware your geese." isa vengeance

"Virtue flies from the heart of a mercenary man." isa consolation
"Virtue flies from the heart of a mercenary man." means \
	"Because I am poor in money I am rich in virtue."
"Virtue flies from the heart of a mercenary man." isa vengeance
"Virtue flies from the heart of a mercenary man." means \
	"When he got money, what else could you expect \
		of him but deterioration?"

